    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-04-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-04-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="876"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d876">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/4215: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Odessa</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_JWL1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Odessa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 2, 1919</hi>, [<hi rend="italic">?</hi>] <hi
                                rend="italic">a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 5, 11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Official news received tonight from Paris that Odessa is to be evacuated.
                    Have arranged for Americans to go aboard British warship tomorrow pending
                    possible arrival of American ship from Constantinople, for which I sent wireless
                    message tonight.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JWL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
